Install aws-cli in ubuntu:::::
1.sudo apt install python3.7
2.python3.7 --version
3.sudo apt-get install python3-pip
4.sudo apt-get install awscli
5.aws --version

configuring aws-cli:::
1.aws configure
2.acccess key:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
3.secret key:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
4.region:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
5.output:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
NOTE:::::::::::Dont share access key and secret key to others.............

For checking aws-cli::::::::;
1.aws s3 ls


terraform installation in ubuntu::::
1.sudo apt-get update
2.sudo apt-get upgrade
3.curl -O https://releases.hashicorp.com/terraform/0.12.25/terraform_0.12.25_linux_amd64.zip
4.unzip -n terraform_0.12.25_linux_amd64.zip -d $HOME/
5.sudo mv $HOME/terraform /usr/local/bin/
6.terraform --version


For checking terraform::
1.create .tf files
2.terraform init----->initializing plugins and moduukes
3.terraform plan----->It will show what we are creating from .tf files in the perticular folder
4.terraform apply---->It will create and change resources
5.terraform destroy--->It will destroy the resources
